  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Preaching of John the Baptist'
      title: The Preaching of John the Baptist
      number: 1
      content: '  The beginning of the [facts regarding the] good news of Jesus Christ,
        the Son of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "As it is written and forever remains in the [writings of the] prophet
        Isaiah:\u201CBehold, I send My messenger ahead of You,Who will prepare Your
        way\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "A voice of one shouting in the wilderness,\u2018Prepare the way of
        the Lord,  Make His paths straight!\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  John the Baptist appeared in the wilderness preaching a baptism
        of repentance for the forgiveness of sins [that is, requiring a change of
        one\u2019s old way of thinking, turning away from sin and seeking God and
        His righteousness]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And all the country of Judea and all the people of Jerusalem were
        continually going out to him; and they were being baptized by him in the
        Jordan River, as they confessed their sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "John wore clothing made of camel\u2019s hair and had a [wide] leather
        band around his waist, and he ate locusts and wild honey. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he was preaching, saying, \u201CAfter me comes He who is mightier
        [more powerful, more noble] than I, and I am not worthy to stoop down and
        untie the straps of His sandals [even as His slave]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Baptism of Jesus'
      title: The Baptism of Jesus
      number: 8
      content: "As for me, I baptized you [who came to me] with water [only]; but
        He will baptize you [who truly repent] with the Holy Spirit.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In those days Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee and was baptized
        by John in the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Immediately coming up out of the water, he (John) saw the heavens
        torn open, and the Spirit like a dove descending on Him (Jesus); '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and a voice came out of heaven saying: \u201CYou are My beloved Son,
        in You I am well-pleased and delighted!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Immediately the [Holy] Spirit forced Him out into the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jesus Preaches in Galilee'
      title: Jesus Preaches in Galilee
      number: 13
      content: 'He was in the wilderness forty days being tempted [to do evil] by
        Satan; and He was with the wild animals, and the angels ministered continually
        to Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now after John [the Baptist] was arrested and  taken into custody,
        Jesus went to Galilee, preaching the good news of [the kingdom of] God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and saying, <JESUS>\u201CThe</JESUS> [appointed period of] <JESUS>time
        is fulfilled, and the kingdom of God is at hand; repent</JESUS> [change your
        inner self\u2014your old way of thinking, regret past sins, live your life
        in a way that proves repentance; seek God\u2019s purpose for your life] <JESUS>and
        believe</JESUS> [with a deep, abiding trust] <JESUS>in the good news</JESUS>
        [regarding salvation].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "As Jesus was walking by the shore of the Sea of Galilee, He saw Simon
        [Peter] and Simon\u2019s brother, Andrew, casting a net in the sea; for they
        were fishermen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>Follow Me</JESUS>
        [as My disciples, accepting Me as your Master and Teacher and walking the
        same path of life that I walk], <JESUS>and I will make you fishers of men.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Immediately they left their nets and followed Him [becoming His disciples,
        believing and trusting in Him and following His example]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Going on a little farther, He saw James the son of Zebedee, and his
        brother John, who were also in the boat mending and cleaning the nets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Immediately Jesus called to them; and they left their father Zebedee
        in the boat with the hired workers, and went away to follow Him [becoming
        His disciples, believing and trusting in Him and following His example].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They went into Capernaum, and immediately on the Sabbath Jesus went
        into the synagogue and began to teach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They were completely amazed at His teaching; because He was teaching
        them as one having [God-given] authority, and not as the scribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Just then there was a man in their synagogue with an unclean spirit;
        and he cried out [terribly from the depths of his throat], '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "saying, \u201CWhat business do You have with us, Jesus of Nazareth?
        Have You come to destroy us? I know who You are\u2014the Holy One of God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus rebuked him, saying, <JESUS>\u201CBe quiet (muzzled, silenced),
        and come out of him!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The unclean spirit threw the man into convulsions, and screeching
        with a loud voice, came out of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "They were all so amazed that they debated and questioned each other,
        saying, \u201CWhat is this? A new teaching with authority! He commands even
        the unclean spirits (demons), and they obey Him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Healing the Crowds'
      title: Healing the Crowds
      number: 28
      content: 'Immediately the news about Him spread everywhere throughout the district
        surrounding Galilee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And immediately they left the synagogue and went into the house of
        Simon [Peter] and Andrew, accompanied by James and John. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now Simon\u2019s mother-in-law was lying sick with a fever; and immediately
        they told Him about her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Jesus went to her, and taking her by the hand, raised her up; and
        the fever left her, and she began to serve them [as her guests].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now when evening came, after the sun had set [and the Sabbath Day
        had ended, in a steady stream] they were bringing to Him all who were sick
        and those who were under the power of demons, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'until the whole city had gathered together at the door. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And Jesus healed many who were suffering with various diseases; and
        He drove out many demons, but would not allow the demons to speak, because
        they knew Him [recognizing Him as the Son of God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Early in the morning, while it was still dark, Jesus got up, left
        [the house], and went out to a secluded place, and was praying there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Simon [Peter] and his companions searched [everywhere, looking anxiously]
        for Him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "and they found Him and said, \u201CEverybody is looking for You!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "He replied, <JESUS>\u201CLet us go on to the neighboring towns, so
        I may preach there also; that is why I came</JESUS> [from the Father].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So He went throughout Galilee, preaching [the gospel] in their synagogues
        and casting out demons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And a leper came to Him, begging Him and falling on his knees before
        Him, saying, \u201CIf You are willing, You are able to make me clean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Moved with compassion [for his suffering], Jesus reached out with
        His hand and touched him, and said to him, <JESUS>\u201CI am willing; be
        cleansed.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The leprosy left him immediately and he was cleansed [completely
        healed and restored to health]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And Jesus [deeply moved] admonished him sternly and sent him away
        immediately, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "saying to him, <JESUS>\u201CSee that you tell no one anything</JESUS>
        [about this]; <JESUS>but go, show yourself to the priest and offer for your
        purification what Moses commanded, as proof to them</JESUS> [that you are
        really healed].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: But he went out and began to proclaim it freely and to spread the
        news [of his healing], to such an extent that Jesus could no longer openly
        enter a city [where He was known], but stayed out in the unpopulated places;
        yet people were still coming to Him from everywhere.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Paralytic Healed'
      title: The Paralytic Healed
      number: 1
      content: '  Jesus returned to Capernaum, and a few days later the news went
        out that He was at home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So many people gathered together that there was no longer room [for
        them], not even near the door; and Jesus was discussing with them the word
        [of God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then they came, bringing to Him a paralyzed man, who was being carried
        by four men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When they were unable to get to Him because of the crowd, they removed
        the roof above Jesus; and when they had dug out an opening, they let down
        the mat on which the paralyzed man was lying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When Jesus saw their [active] faith [springing from confidence in
        Him], He said to the paralyzed man, <JESUS>\u201CSon, your sins are forgiven.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But some of the scribes were sitting there debating in their hearts
        [the implication of what He had said], '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CWhy does this man talk that way? He is blaspheming; who can
        forgive sins [remove guilt, nullify sin\u2019s penalty, and assign righteousness]
        except God alone?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Immediately Jesus, being fully aware [of their hostility] and knowing
        in His spirit that they were thinking this, said to them, <JESUS>\u201CWhy
        are you debating </JESUS>and arguing about these things in your hearts?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>Which is easier, to say to the paralyzed man, \u2018Your sins
        are forgiven\u2019; or to say, \u2018Get up, and pick up your mat and walk\u2019?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>But so that you may know that the </JESUS><JESUS>Son of Man
        has the authority </JESUS>and power on earth to forgive sins\u201D\u2014He
        said to the paralyzed man, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI say to you, get up, pick up your mat and go home.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he got up and immediately picked up the mat and went out before
        them all, so that they all were astonished and they glorified and praised
        God, saying, \u201CWe have never seen anything like this!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Levi (Matthew) Called'
      title: Levi (Matthew) Called
      number: 13
      content: 'Jesus went out again along the [Galilean] seashore; and all the people
        were coming to Him, and He was teaching them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "As He was passing by, He saw Levi (Matthew) the son of Alphaeus sitting
        in the tax collector\u2019s booth, and He said to him, <JESUS>\u201CFollow
        Me</JESUS> [as My disciple, accepting Me as your Master and Teacher and walking
        the same path of life that I walk].\u201D And he got up and followed Him
        [becoming His disciple, believing and trusting in Him and following His example].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And it happened that Jesus was reclining at the table in Levi\u2019s
        house, and many tax collectors and sinners [including non-observant Jews]
        were eating with Him and His disciples; for there were many of them and they
        were following Him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the scribes [belonging to the sect] of the Pharisees saw that
        Jesus was eating with the sinners [including non-observant Jews] and tax
        collectors, they asked His disciples, \u201CWhy does He eat and drink with
        tax collectors and sinners?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When Jesus heard this, He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CThose who are
        healthy have no need of a physician, but</JESUS> [only] <JESUS>those who
        are sick; I did not come to call the righteous, but sinners</JESUS> [who
        recognize their sin and humbly seek forgiveness].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now John\u2019s disciples and the Pharisees were fasting [as a ritual];
        and they came and asked Jesus, \u201CWhy are John\u2019s disciples and the
        disciples of the Pharisees fasting, but Your disciples are not doing so?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CThe attendants of the bridegroom </JESUS><JESUS>cannot
        fast while the bridegroom is</JESUS> [still] <JESUS>with them, can they?
        As long as they have the bridegroom with them, they cannot fast.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>But the days will come when the bridegroom is</JESUS> [forcefully]
        <JESUS>taken away from them, and they will fast at that time.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNo one sews a patch of unshrunk (new) cloth on an
        old garment; otherwise the patch pulls away from it, the new from the old,
        and the tear becomes worse.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Question of the Sabbath'
      title: Question of the Sabbath
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>No one puts new wine into old </JESUS><JESUS>wineskins; otherwise
        the</JESUS> [fermenting] <JESUS>wine will</JESUS> [expand and] <JESUS>burst
        the skins, and the wine is lost as well as the wineskins. But new wine must
        be put into new wineskins.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'One Sabbath He was walking along [with His disciples] through the
        grainfields, and as they went along, His disciples began picking the heads
        of grain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The Pharisees said to Him, \u201CLook, why are they doing what is
        unlawful on the Sabbath?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CHave you never read</JESUS> [in
        the Scriptures] <JESUS>what David did when he was in need and was hungry,
        he and his companions;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>how he went into the house of God in the time of Abiathar
        the high priest, and ate the sacred bread, which is not lawful for anyone
        but the priests to eat, and how he also gave it to the men who were with
        him?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CThe Sabbath was made for man, not
        man for the Sabbath.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>So the Son of Man is Lord even of the Sabbath</JESUS> [and
        He has authority over it].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath'
      title: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath
      number: 1
      content: '  Again Jesus went into a synagogue; and a man was there whose hand
        was withered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Pharisees were watching Jesus closely to see if He would heal
        him on the Sabbath, so that they might accuse Him [in the Jewish high court]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He said to the man whose hand was withered, <JESUS>\u201CGet up and
        come forward!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He asked them, <JESUS>\u201CIs it lawful on the Sabbath to do good
        or to do evil, to save a life or to kill?\u201D</JESUS> But they kept silent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "After looking around at them with anger, grieved at the hardness
        and arrogance of their hearts, He told the man, <JESUS>\u201CHold out your
        hand.\u201D</JESUS> And he held it out, and his hand was [completely] restored. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Pharisees went out and immediately began conspiring with
        the Herodians [to plot] against Him, as to how they might [fabricate some
        legal grounds to] put Him to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Jesus withdrew to the sea with His disciples; and a large crowd from
        Galilee followed Him; and also people from Judea, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and from Jerusalem, and from Idumea, and [from the region] beyond
        the Jordan, and around Tyre and Sidon; a vast number of people came to Him
        because they were hearing about all [the things] that He was doing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And He told His disciples to have a small boat stand ready for Him
        because of the many people, so that they would not crowd Him; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'for He had healed many, and as a result all who had diseases pressed
        around Him to touch Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Whenever the unclean spirits saw Him, they fell down before Him and
        screamed out, \u201CYou are the Son of God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Twelve Are Chosen'
      title: The Twelve Are Chosen
      number: 12
      content: 'Jesus sternly warned them [again and again] not to tell who He was.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He went up on the hillside and called those whom He Himself wanted
        and chose; and they came to Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And He appointed twelve [disciples], so that they would be with Him
        [for instruction] and so that He could send them out to preach [the gospel
        as apostles\u2014that is, as His special messengers, personally chosen representatives], "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and to have authority and power to cast out demons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He appointed the twelve: Simon (to whom He gave the name Peter), '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and James, the son of Zebedee, and John the brother of James (to
        them He gave the name Boanerges, that is, \u201CSons of Thunder\u201D); "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and [He also appointed] Andrew, and Philip, and Bartholomew (Nathanael),
        and Matthew (Levi the tax collector), and Thomas, and James the son of Alphaeus,
        and Thaddaeus (Judas the son of James), and Simon the Zealot; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and Judas Iscariot, who betrayed Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then He came to a house [in Capernaum], and a crowd formed again,
        so [many people] that Jesus and His disciples could not even eat a meal [together]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "When His own family heard this they went to take custody of Him;
        for they were saying, \u201CHe is out of His mind.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The scribes who came down from Jerusalem were saying, \u201CHe is
        possessed by Beelzebul (Satan),\u201D and \u201CHe is driving out the demons
        by the [power of the] ruler of the demons.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So He called them to Himself and spoke to them in parables, <JESUS>\u201CHow
        can Satan drive out Satan?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '<JESUS>If a kingdom is divided</JESUS> [split into factions and rebelling]
        <JESUS>against itself, that kingdom cannot stand.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>And if a house is divided against itself, that house cannot
        stand.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>And if Satan has risen up against himself and is divided,
        he cannot stand, but is coming to an end.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>But no one can go into a strong man\u2019s house and steal
        his property unless he first overpowers </JESUS>and ties up the strong man,
        and then he will ransack and rob his house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you,
        all sins will be forgiven the sons of men, and all the abusive and blasphemous
        things they say;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>but whoever </JESUS><JESUS>blasphemes against the Holy Spirit
        </JESUS>and His power [by attributing the miracles done by Me to Satan] <JESUS>never
        has forgiveness, but is guilty of an everlasting sin</JESUS> [a sin which
        is unforgivable in this present age as well as in the age to come]\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "[Jesus said this] because the scribes and Pharisees were [attributing
        His miracles to Satan by] saying, \u201CHe has an unclean spirit.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then His mother and His brothers arrived, and standing outside they
        sent word to Him and called for Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "A crowd was sitting around Him, and they said to Him, \u201CLook!
        Your mother and Your brothers are outside asking for You.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And He replied, <JESUS>\u201CWho are My mother and My brothers?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Looking at those who were sitting in a circle around Him, He said,
        <JESUS>\u201CHere are My mother and My brothers!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>For </JESUS><JESUS>whoever does the will of God</JESUS> [by
        believing in Me, and following Me], <JESUS>he is My brother and sister and
        mother.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Parable of the Sower and Soils'
      title: Parable of the Sower and Soils
      number: 1
      content: '  Again Jesus began to teach beside the sea [of Galilee]. And a very
        large crowd gathered around Him, so He got into a boat [anchoring it a short
        distance out] on the sea and sat down; and the whole crowd was by the sea
        on the shore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And He taught them many things in parables, and in His teaching He
        said to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CListen! A sower went out to sow </JESUS>seed;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>and as he was sowing, some </JESUS>seed fell by the road,
        and the birds came and ate it up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '<JESUS>Other </JESUS>seed fell on rocks where there was not much
        soil; and immediately a plant sprang up <JESUS>because the soil had no depth.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>And when the sun came up, the plant was scorched; and because
        it had no root, it dried up </JESUS>and withered away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>Other </JESUS>seed fell among thorns, and the thorns came
        up and choked it, and it yielded no grain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>And other </JESUS>seed fell into good soil, and as the plants
        grew and increased, they yielded a crop and produced thirty, sixty, and a
        hundred times [as much as had been sown].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And He said, <JESUS>\u201CHe who has ears to hear, let him hear </JESUS>and
        heed My words.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As soon as He was alone, those who were around Him, together with
        the twelve [disciples], began asking Him about [the interpretation of] the
        parables. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CThe mystery of the kingdom of God has
        been given to you</JESUS> [who have teachable hearts], <JESUS>but those who
        are outside</JESUS> [the unbelievers, the spiritually blind] <JESUS>get everything
        in parables,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Explanation'
      title: Explanation
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>so that </JESUS>they will continually look but not see, and
        they will continually hear but not understand, otherwise they might turn 
        [from their rejection of the truth] <JESUS>and be forgiven</JESUS>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CDo you not understand this parable?
        How will you understand </JESUS>and grasp the meaning of all the parables?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>The sower sows the word</JESUS> [of God, the good news regarding
        the way of salvation]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>These</JESUS> [in the first group] <JESUS>are the ones along
        the road where the word is sown; but when they hear, Satan immediately comes
        and takes away the word which has been sown in them.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>In a similar way these</JESUS> [in the second group] <JESUS>are
        the ones on whom seed was sown on rocky ground, who, when they hear the word,
        immediately receive it with joy</JESUS> [but accept it only superficially]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>and they have no real root in themselves, so they endure only
        for a little while; then, when trouble or persecution comes because of the
        word, immediately they</JESUS> [are offended and displeased at being associated
        with Me and] <JESUS>stumble </JESUS>and fall away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>And others are the ones on whom seed was sown among the thorns;
        these are the ones who have heard the word,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>but the worries </JESUS>and cares of the world [the distractions
        of this age with its worldly pleasures], <JESUS>and the deceitfulness</JESUS>
        [and the false security or glamour] <JESUS>of wealth</JESUS> [or fame], <JESUS>and
        the passionate desires for all the other things creep in and choke out the
        word, and it becomes unfruitful.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>And those</JESUS> [in the last group] <JESUS>are the ones
        on whom seed was sown on the good soil; and they hear the word</JESUS> [of
        God, the good news regarding the way of salvation] <JESUS>and accept it and
        bear fruit\u2014thirty, sixty, and a hundred times as much</JESUS> [as was
        sown].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CA lamp is not brought in to be put
        under a basket or under a bed, is it? Is it not</JESUS> [brought in] <JESUS>to
        be put on the lampstand?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>For nothing is hidden, except to be revealed; nor has anything
        been kept secret, but that it would come to light</JESUS> [that is, things
        are hidden only temporarily, until the appropriate time comes for them to
        be known]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>If anyone has ears to hear, let him hear </JESUS>and heed
        My words.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CPay attention to what you hear.
        By your own standard of measurement</JESUS> [that is, to the extent that
        you study spiritual truth and apply godly wisdom] <JESUS>it will be measured
        to you</JESUS> [and you will be given even greater ability to respond]<JESUS>\u2014and
        more will be given to you besides.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Parable of the Seed'
      title: Parable of the Seed
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>For </JESUS><JESUS>whoever has</JESUS> [a teachable heart],
        <JESUS>to him </JESUS>more [understanding] <JESUS>will be given; and whoever
        does not have</JESUS> [a yearning for truth], <JESUS>even what he has will
        be taken away from him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then He said, <JESUS>\u201CThe kingdom of God is like a man who throws
        seed on the ground;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>and he goes to bed at night and gets up every day, and</JESUS>
        [in the meantime] <JESUS>the seed sprouts and grows; how</JESUS> [it does
        this], <JESUS>he does not know.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>The earth produces crops by itself; first the blade, then
        the head</JESUS> [of grain], <JESUS>then the mature grain in the head.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Parable of the Mustard Seed'
      title: Parable of the Mustard Seed
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>But when the crop ripens, he immediately puts in the sickle</JESUS>
        [to reap], <JESUS>because</JESUS> [the time for] <JESUS>the harvest has come.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And He said, <JESUS>\u201CHow shall we </JESUS><JESUS>picture the
        kingdom of God, or what parable shall we use to illustrate </JESUS>and explain
        it?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '<JESUS>It is like a mustard seed, which, when it is sown on the ground,
        even though it is </JESUS><JESUS>smaller than all the</JESUS> [other] <JESUS>seeds
        that are</JESUS> [sown] <JESUS>on the soil,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>yet when it is sown, it grows up and becomes larger than all
        the garden herbs; and it puts out large branches, so that </JESUS>the birds
        of the sky are able to make nests  and  live under its shade.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'With many such parables, Jesus spoke the word to them, as they were
        able to hear and understand it; '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Jesus Stills the Sea'
      title: Jesus Stills the Sea
      number: 34
      content: 'and He did not say anything to them without [using] a parable; He
        did, however, explain everything privately to His own disciples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "On that [same] day, when evening had come, He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CLet
        us go over to the other side</JESUS> [of the Sea of Galilee].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'So leaving the crowd, they took Him with them, just as He was, in
        the boat. And other boats were with Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And a fierce windstorm began to blow, and waves were breaking over
        the boat, so that it was already being swamped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But Jesus was in the stern, asleep [with His head] on the [sailor\u2019s
        leather] cushion. And they woke Him and said to Him, \u201CTeacher, do You
        not care that we are about to die?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And He got up and [sternly] rebuked the wind and said to the sea,
        <JESUS>\u201CHush, be still (muzzled)!\u201D</JESUS> And the wind died down
        [as if it had grown weary] and there was [at once] a great calm [a perfect
        peacefulness]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CWhy are you afraid? Do you still
        have no faith </JESUS>and confidence [in Me]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "They were filled with great fear, and said to each other, \u201CWho
        then is this, that even the wind and the sea obey Him?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Gerasene Demoniac'
      title: The Gerasene Demoniac
      number: 1
      content: '  They came to the other side of the sea, to the region of the Gerasenes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When Jesus got out of the boat, immediately a man from the tombs
        with an unclean spirit met Him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the man lived in the tombs, and no one could bind him anymore,
        not even with chains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For he had often been bound with shackles [for the feet] and with
        chains, and he tore apart the chains and broke the shackles into pieces,
        and no one was strong enough to subdue and tame him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Night and day he was constantly screaming and shrieking among the
        tombs and on the mountains, and cutting himself with [sharp] stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Seeing Jesus from a distance, he ran up and bowed down before Him
        [in homage]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and screaming with a loud voice, he said, \u201CWhat business do
        we have in common with each other, Jesus, Son of the Most High God? I implore
        you by God [swear to me], do not torment me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For Jesus had been saying to him, <JESUS>\u201CCome out of the man,
        you unclean spirit!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He was asking him, <JESUS>\u201CWhat is your name?\u201D</JESUS>
        And he replied, \u201CMy name is Legion; for we are many.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he began begging Him repeatedly not to send them out of the region. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now there was a large herd of pigs grazing there on the mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the demons begged Him, saying, \u201CSend us to the pigs so that
        we may go into them!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jesus gave them permission. And the unclean spirits came out [of
        the man] and entered the pigs. The herd, numbering about two thousand, rushed
        down the steep bank into the sea; and they were drowned [one after the other]
        in the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The herdsmen [tending the pigs] ran away and reported it in the city
        and in the country. And the people came to see what had happened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "They came to Jesus and saw the man who had been demon-possessed sitting
        down, clothed and in his right mind, the man who had [previously] had the
        \u201Clegion\u201D [of demons]; and they were frightened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Those who had seen it described [in detail] to the people what had
        happened to the demon-possessed man, and [told them all] about the pigs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the people began to beg with Jesus to leave their region. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'As He was stepping into the boat, the [Gentile] man who had been
        demon-possessed was begging with Him [asking] that he might go with Him [as
        a disciple]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus did not let him [come], but [instead] He said to him, <JESUS>\u201CGo
        home to your family and tell them all the great things that the Lord has
        done for you, and how He has had mercy on you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Miracles and Healing'
      title: Miracles and Healing
      number: 20
      content: 'So he [obeyed and] went away and began to publicly proclaim in Decapolis
        [the region of the ten Hellenistic cities] all the great things that Jesus
        had done for him; and all the people were astonished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Jesus had again crossed over in the boat to the other side [of
        the sea], a large crowd gathered around Him; and so He stayed by the seashore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'One of the synagogue officials named Jairus came up; and seeing Him,
        fell at His feet '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and begged anxiously with Him, saying, \u201CMy little daughter is
        at the point of death; [please] come and lay Your hands on her, so that she
        will be healed and live.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Jesus went with him; and a large crowd followed Him and pressed
        in around Him [from all sides].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'A woman [in the crowd] had [suffered from] a hemorrhage for twelve
        years, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and had endured much [suffering] at the hands of many physicians.
        She had spent all that she had and was not helped at all, but instead had
        become worse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'She had heard [reports] about Jesus, and she came up behind Him in
        the crowd and touched His outer robe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For she thought, \u201CIf I just touch His clothing, I will get well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Immediately her flow of blood was dried up; and she felt in her body
        [and knew without any doubt] that she was healed of her suffering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Immediately Jesus, recognizing in Himself that power had gone out
        from Him, turned around in the crowd and asked, <JESUS>\u201CWho touched
        My clothes?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "His disciples said to Him, \u201CYou see the crowd pressing in around
        You [from all sides], and You ask, \u2018Who touched Me?\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Still He kept looking around to see the woman who had done it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the woman, though she was afraid and trembling, aware of what
        had happened to her, came and fell down before Him and told Him the whole
        truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then He said to her, <JESUS>\u201CDaughter, your faith</JESUS> [your
        personal trust and confidence in Me] <JESUS>has restored you to health; go
        in peace and be</JESUS> [permanently] <JESUS>healed from your suffering.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "While He was still speaking, some people came from the synagogue
        official\u2019s house, saying [to Jairus], \u201CYour daughter has died;
        why bother the Teacher any longer?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Overhearing what was being said, Jesus said to the synagogue official,
        <JESUS>\u201CDo not be afraid; only keep on believing</JESUS> [in Me and
        my power].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And He allowed no one to go with Him [as witnesses], except Peter
        and James and John the brother of James. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'They came to the house of the synagogue official; and He looked [with
        understanding] at the uproar and commotion, and people loudly weeping and
        wailing [in mourning]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "When He had gone in, He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CWhy make a commotion
        and weep? The child has not died, but is sleeping.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "They began laughing [scornfully] at Him [because they knew the child
        was dead]. But He made them all go outside, and took along the child\u2019s
        father and mother and His own [three] companions, and entered the room where
        the child was. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Taking the child\u2019s hand, He said [tenderly] to her, <JESUS>\u201CTalitha
        kum!\u201D</JESUS>\u2014which translated [from Aramaic] means, <JESUS>\u201CLittle
        girl, I say to you, get up!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "The little girl immediately got up and began to walk, for she was
        twelve years old. And immediately they [who witnessed the child\u2019s resurrection]
        were overcome with great wonder and utter amazement. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: He gave strict orders that no one should know about this, and He told
        them to give her something to eat.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Teaching at Nazareth'
      title: Teaching at Nazareth
      number: 1
      content: '  Jesus left there and came to His hometown [Nazareth]; and His disciples
        followed Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When the Sabbath came, He began to teach in the synagogue; and many
        who listened to Him were astonished, saying, \u201CWhere did this man get
        these things [this knowledge and spiritual insight]? What is this wisdom
        [this confident understanding of the Scripture] that has been given to Him,
        and such miracles as these performed by His hands? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Is this not the carpenter, the son of Mary, and the brother of James
        and Joses and Judas and Simon? Are His sisters not here with us?\u201D And
        they were [deeply] offended by Him [and their disapproval blinded them to
        the fact that He was anointed by God as the Messiah]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CA prophet is not without honor (respect)
        except in his hometown and among his relatives and in his own household.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And He could not do a miracle there at all [because of their unbelief]
        except that He laid His hands on a few sick people and healed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Twelve Sent Out'
      title: The Twelve Sent Out
      number: 6
      content: 'He wondered at their unbelief.  And He was going around in the villages
        teaching.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And He called the twelve [disciples] and began to send them out [as
        His special messengers] two by two, and gave them authority and power over
        the unclean spirits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "He told them to take nothing for the journey except a mere walking
        stick\u2014no bread, no [traveler\u2019s] bag, no money in their belts\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'but to wear sandals; and [He told them] not to wear two tunics. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And He told them, <JESUS>\u201CWherever you go into a house, stay
        there until you leave that town.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>Any place that does not welcome you or listen to you, when
        you leave there, </JESUS><JESUS>shake the dust off the soles of your feet
        as a testimony against them</JESUS> [breaking all ties with them because
        they rejected My message].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So they went out and preached that men should repent [that is, think
        differently, recognize sin, turn away from it, and live changed lives]. '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: John\u2019s Fate Recalled"
      title: "John\u2019s Fate Recalled"
      number: 13
      content: 'And they were casting out many demons and were anointing with oil
        many who were sick, and healing them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "King Herod [Antipas] heard about this, for Jesus\u2019 name and reputation
        had become well known. People were saying, \u201CJohn the Baptist has been
        raised from the dead, and that is why these miraculous powers are at work
        in Him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But others were saying, \u201CHe is Elijah!\u201D And others were
        saying, \u201CIt is a prophet, like one of the prophets [of old].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But when Herod heard [of it], he kept saying, \u201CJohn, whom I
        beheaded, has risen [from the dead]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For Herod himself had sent [guards] and had John arrested and shackled
        in prison because of Herodias, the wife of his [half-] brother Philip, because
        he (Herod) had married her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For John had been saying to Herod, \u201CIt is not lawful [under
        Mosaic Law] for you to have your brother\u2019s wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Herodias had a grudge against John and wanted to kill him, but she
        could not, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'because Herod feared John, knowing that he was a righteous and holy
        man, and he continually kept him safe. When he heard John [speak], he was
        very perplexed; but he enjoyed listening to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But an opportune time [finally] came [for Herodias]. Herod on his
        birthday gave a banquet for his officials (nobles, courtiers) and military
        commanders and the leading men of Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now [Salome] the daughter of Herodias came in and danced [for the
        men]. She pleased and beguiled Herod and his dinner guests; and the king
        said to the girl, \u201CAsk me for whatever you want and I will give it to
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he swore to her, \u201CWhatever you ask me, I will give it to
        you; up to half of my kingdom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "She went out and said to her mother, \u201CWhat shall I ask for?\u201D
        And Herodias replied, \u201CThe head of John the Baptist!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And she rushed back to the king and asked, saying, \u201CI want you
        to give me right now the head of John the Baptist on a platter!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The king was deeply grieved, but because of his oaths and his dinner
        guests [who might have regarded him as weak], he was unwilling to [break
        his word and] refuse her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So the king immediately sent for an executioner and commanded him
        to bring back John\u2019s head. And he went and had John beheaded in the
        prison, "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and brought back his head on a platter, and gave it to the girl;
        and the girl gave it to her mother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Five Thousand Fed'
      title: Five Thousand Fed
      number: 29
      content: "When his disciples heard about this, they came and took away John\u2019s
        body and laid it in a tomb.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The apostles [who had been sent out on a mission] gathered together
        with Jesus and told Him everything that they had done and taught. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CCome away by yourselves to a secluded
        place and rest a little while\u201D</JESUS>\u2014for there were many [people
        who were continually] coming and going, and they could not even find time
        to eat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And they went away by themselves in the boat to a secluded place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Many [people] saw them leaving, and recognized them and ran there
        together on foot from all the [surrounding] cities, and got there ahead of
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'When Jesus went ashore, He saw a large crowd [waiting], and He was
        moved with compassion for them because they were like sheep without a shepherd
        [lacking guidance]; and He began to teach them many things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "When the day was nearly gone, His disciples came to Him and said,
        \u201CThis is an isolated place, and it is already late; "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "send the crowds away so that they may go into the surrounding countryside
        and villages and buy themselves something to eat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "But He replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou give them something to eat!\u201D</JESUS>
        And they asked Him, \u201CShall we go and buy 200 denarii worth of bread
        and give it to them to eat?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CHow many loaves do you have? Go look!\u201D</JESUS>
        And when they found out, they said, \u201CFive [loaves], and two fish.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Then Jesus commanded them all to sit down by groups on the green
        grass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'They sat down in groups of hundreds and of fifties [so that the crowd
        resembled an orderly arrangement of colorful garden plots]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Taking the five loaves and two fish, He looked up to heaven and said
        a blessing [of praise and thanksgiving to the Father]. Then He broke the
        loaves and [repeatedly] gave them to the disciples to set before the people;
        and He divided up the two fish among them all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'They all ate and were satisfied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And the disciples picked up twelve full baskets of the broken pieces
        [of the loaves], and of the fish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: Jesus Walks on the Water'
      title: Jesus Walks on the Water
      number: 44
      content: 'Those who ate the loaves were five thousand men [not counting the
        women and children].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Jesus immediately insisted that His disciples get into the boat and
        go ahead [of Him] to the other side to Bethsaida, while He was dismissing
        the crowd. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'And after He said goodbye to them, He went to the mountain to pray.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Now when evening had come, the boat was in the middle of the sea,
        and Jesus was alone on the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Seeing the disciples straining at the oars, because the wind was
        against them, at about the fourth watch of the night (3:00-6:00 a.m.) He
        came to them, walking on the sea. And [acted as if] He intended to pass by
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'But when they saw Him walking on the sea, they thought it was a ghost,
        and cried out [in horror]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "for they all saw Him and were shaken and terrified. But He immediately
        spoke with them and said, <JESUS>\u201CTake courage! It is I (I AM)! Stop
        being afraid.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Then He got into the boat with them, and the wind ceased [as if exhausted
        by its own activity]; and they were completely overwhelmed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: Healing at Gennesaret'
      title: Healing at Gennesaret
      number: 52
      content: 'because they had not understood [the miracle of] the loaves [how
        it revealed the power and deity of Jesus]; but [in fact] their heart was
        hardened [being oblivious and indifferent to His amazing works].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'When they had crossed over [the sea], they reached the land of Gennesaret
        and anchored at the shore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'They got out of the boat and immediately people recognized Him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'and ran throughout that surrounding countryside and began to carry
        around on their mats those who were sick, to any place where they heard He
        was. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: And wherever He came into villages, or cities, or the countryside,
        they were laying the sick in the market places and pleading with Him [to
        allow them] just to touch the fringe (tassel with a blue cord) of His robe;
        and all who touched it were healed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Followers of Tradition'
      title: Followers of Tradition
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Pharisees and some of the scribes came from Jerusalem and
        gathered around Him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and they had seen that some of His disciples ate their bread with
        [ceremonially] impure hands, that is, unwashed [and defiled according to
        Jewish religious ritual]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '(For the Pharisees and all of the Jews do not eat unless they carefully
        wash their hands, holding firmly to the traditions of the elders; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and when they come from the market place, they do not eat unless
        they cleanse themselves [completely according to ritual]; and there are many
        other things [oral, man-made laws and traditions handed down to them] which
        they follow diligently, such as the washing of cups and pitchers and copper
        utensils.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So the Pharisees and scribes asked Jesus, \u201CWhy do Your disciples
        not live their lives according to the tradition of the elders, but [instead]
        eat their bread with [ceremonially] unwashed hands?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He replied, <JESUS>\u201CRightly did Isaiah prophesy about you hypocrites
        (play-actors, pretenders), as it is written</JESUS> [in Scripture],  <JESUS>\u2018T</JESUS>hese
        people honor Me with their lips,  <JESUS>B</JESUS>ut their heart is far from
        Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  <JESUS>T</JESUS>hey worship Me in vain  [their worship is meaningless
        and worthless, a pretense],  <JESUS>T</JESUS>eaching the precepts of men
        as doctrines [giving their traditions equal weight with the Scriptures].\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  <JESUS>You disregard </JESUS>and neglect the commandment of God,
        and cling [faithfully] <JESUS>to the tradition of men.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He was also saying to them, <JESUS>\u201CYou are experts at setting
        aside </JESUS>and nullifying the commandment of God in order to keep your
        [man-made] <JESUS>tradition </JESUS>and regulations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>For Moses said, \u2018H</JESUS>onor your father and your mother
        [with respect and gratitude]\u2019; <JESUS>and, \u2018H</JESUS>e who speaks
        evil of his father or mother must be put to death\u2019;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>but you</JESUS> [Pharisees and scribes] <JESUS>say, \u2018If
        a man tells his father or mother, \u201CWhatever I have that would help you
        is Corban,</JESUS> (that is to say, already a gift to God),\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>then you no longer let him do anything for his father or mother</JESUS>
        [since helping them would violate his vow of Corban]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Heart of Man'
      title: The Heart of Man
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>so you nullify the</JESUS> [authority of the] <JESUS>word
        of God</JESUS> [acting as if it did not apply] <JESUS>because of your tradition
        which you have handed down</JESUS> [through the elders]. <JESUS>And you do
        many things such as that.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "After He called the people to Him again, He began saying to them,
        <JESUS>\u201CListen</JESUS> [carefully] <JESUS>to Me, all of you,</JESUS>
        [hear] <JESUS>and understand</JESUS> [what I am saying]: "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>there is nothing outside a man</JESUS> [such as food] <JESUS>which
        by going into him can defile him</JESUS> [morally or spiritually]; <JESUS>but
        the things which come out of</JESUS> [the heart of] <JESUS>a man are what
        defile </JESUS>and dishonor him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>[</JESUS>If anyone has ears to hear, let him hear.\u201D]  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When Jesus had left the crowd and gone into the house, His disciples
        asked Him about the parable. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CAre you, too, so foolish </JESUS>and
        lacking in understanding? Do you not understand that whatever goes into the
        man from outside cannot defile and dishonor him,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>since it does not enter his heart, but</JESUS> [only] <JESUS>his
        stomach, and</JESUS> [from there it] <JESUS>is eliminated?\u201D</JESUS>
        (By this, He declared all foods ceremonially clean.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And He said, <JESUS>\u201CWhatever comes from</JESUS> [the heart
        of] <JESUS>a man, that is what defiles </JESUS>and dishonors him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>For from within,</JESUS> [that is] <JESUS>out the heart of
        men, come base </JESUS>and malevolent thoughts and schemes, acts of sexual
        immorality, thefts, murders, adulteries,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>acts of greed </JESUS>and covetousness, wickedness, deceit,
        unrestrained conduct, envy and jealousy, slander and profanity, arrogance
        and self-righteousness and foolishness (poor judgment).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The Syrophoenician Woman'
      title: The Syrophoenician Woman
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>All these evil things</JESUS> [schemes and desires] <JESUS>come
        from within and defile </JESUS>and dishonor the man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Jesus got up and left there and went to the region of Tyre [and Sidon,
        the coastal area of Phoenicia]. He entered a house and did not want anyone
        to know about it; but it was impossible for Him to be hidden [from the public]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Instead, after hearing about Him, a woman whose little daughter had
        an unclean spirit immediately came and fell at His feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the woman was a Gentile (Greek), a Syrophoenician by nationality.
        And she kept pleading with Him to drive the demon out of her daughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He was saying to her, <JESUS>\u201CFirst let the children</JESUS>
        [of Israel] <JESUS>be fed, for it is not right to take the children\u2019s
        bread and throw it to the </JESUS><JESUS>pet dogs (non-Jews).\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But she replied, \u201CYes, Lord, but even the pet dogs under the
        table eat the children\u2019s crumbs.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And He said to her, <JESUS>\u201CBecause of this answer</JESUS> [reflecting
        your humility and faith], <JESUS>go</JESUS> [knowing that your request is
        granted]; <JESUS>the demon has left your daughter</JESUS> [permanently].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And returning to her home, she found the child lying on the couch
        [relaxed and resting], the demon having gone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Soon after this Jesus left the region of Tyre, and passed through
        Sidon to the Sea of Galilee, through the region of Decapolis [the ten Hellenistic
        cities]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'They brought to Him a man who was deaf and had difficulty speaking,
        and they begged Jesus to place His hand on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Jesus, taking him aside by himself, away from the crowd, put His
        fingers into the man\u2019s ears, and after spitting, He touched the man\u2019s
        tongue [with the saliva]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "and looking up to heaven, He sighed deeply and said to the man, <JESUS>\u201CEphphatha,\u201D</JESUS>
        which [in Aramaic] means, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>Be opened </JESUS>and
        released!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And his ears were opened, his tongue was released, and he began speaking
        plainly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Jesus commanded them not to tell anyone; but the more He ordered
        them, the more widely they continued to proclaim it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "They were thoroughly astounded and completely overwhelmed, saying,
        \u201CHe has done everything well! He even makes the deaf hear and the mute
        speak!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Four Thousand Fed'
      title: Four Thousand Fed
      number: 1
      content: '  In those days, when there was again a large crowd [gathered before
        Him] and they had nothing to eat, Jesus called His disciples and told them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI feel compassion for the crowd; they have been with
        Me now for three days and have nothing</JESUS> [left] <JESUS>to eat.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>If I send them away to their homes hungry, they will faint</JESUS>
        [from exhaustion] <JESUS>on the road; because some of them have come a long
        way.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "His disciples replied to Him, \u201CWhere will anyone be able to
        find enough bread here in this isolated place to feed these people?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He asked them, <JESUS>\u201CHow many loaves</JESUS> [of bread] <JESUS>do
        you have?\u201D</JESUS> They said, \u201CSeven.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He directed the people to sit down on the ground; and taking the
        seven loaves, He gave thanks and broke them, and [repeatedly] gave them to
        His disciples to set before them, and they served the crowd. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They also had a few small fish; and when Jesus had blessed them [and
        given thanks], He ordered these [fish] to be set before them as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the people ate and were satisfied; and they picked up seven large
        baskets full of the broken pieces that were left over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'About four thousand [men] were there [besides women and children];
        and He sent them away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then immediately He got into the boat with His disciples and went
        to the district of Dalmanutha.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The Pharisees came out and began to argue [contentiously and debate]
        with Him, demanding from Him a sign from heaven, to test Him [because of
        their unbelief]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He groaned and sighed deeply in His spirit and said, <JESUS>\u201CWhy
        does this generation demand a sign? I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly
        say to you, <JESUS>no sign will be given to this generation!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Leaving them, He again boarded the boat and left for the other side.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now the disciples had forgotten to bring bread, and they had only
        one loaf with them in the boat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Jesus repeatedly ordered them, saying, <JESUS>\u201CWatch out! Beware
        of the </JESUS><JESUS>leaven of the Pharisees and the leaven of Herod.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "They began discussing this with one another, saying, \u201CIt is
        because we have no bread [that He said this].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus, aware of this [discussion], said to them, <JESUS>\u201CWhy
        are you discussing</JESUS> [the fact] <JESUS>that you have no bread? Do you
        still not see or understand? Are your hearts hardened?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>T</JESUS>hough you have eyes, do you not see? And though you
        have ears, do you not hear  and  listen [to what I have said]? <JESUS>And
        do you not remember,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>when I broke the five loaves for the five thousand, how many
        baskets full of broken pieces you picked up?\u201D</JESUS> They answered,
        \u201CTwelve.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAnd</JESUS> [when I broke] <JESUS>the seven</JESUS>
        [loaves] <JESUS>for the four thousand, how many large baskets full of broken
        pieces did you pick up?\u201D</JESUS> And they answered, \u201CSeven.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And He was saying to them, <JESUS>\u201CDo you still not understand?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then they came to Bethsaida; and some people brought a blind man
        to Jesus and begged Him to touch him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Taking the blind man by the hand, He led him out of the village;
        and after spitting on his eyes and laying His hands on him, He asked him,
        <JESUS>\u201CDo you see anything?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And he looked up and said, \u201CI see people, but [they look] like
        trees, walking around.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then again Jesus laid His hands on his eyes; and the man stared intently
        and [his sight] was [completely] restored, and he began to see everything
        clearly. '
      comments: []
    - name: "26: Peter\u2019s Confession of Christ"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Confession of Christ"
      number: 26
      content: "And He sent him to his home, saying, <JESUS>\u201CDo not even enter
        the village.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then Jesus and His disciples went out to the villages of Caesarea
        Philippi; and on the way He asked His disciples, <JESUS>\u201CWho do people
        say that I am?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "They answered Him, \u201CJohn the Baptist; and others say Elijah;
        but others, one of the prophets.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And He asked them, <JESUS>\u201CBut who do you say that I am?\u201D</JESUS>
        Peter replied to Him, \u201CYou [in contrast to the others] are the Christ
        (the Messiah, the Anointed).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Jesus strictly warned them not to tell anyone about Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And He began to teach them that the Son of Man must [of necessity]
        suffer many things and be rejected [as the Messiah] by the elders and the
        chief priests and the scribes, and must be put to death, and after three
        days rise [from death to life]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He was stating the matter plainly [not holding anything back]. Then
        Peter took Him aside and began to reprimand Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "But turning around [with His back to Peter] and seeing His disciples,
        He rebuked Peter, saying, <JESUS>\u201CGet behind Me, Satan; for your mind
        is not set on God\u2019s will </JESUS>or His values and purposes, but on
        what pleases man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus called the crowd together with His disciples, and said to them,
        <JESUS>\u201CIf anyone wishes to follow Me</JESUS> [as My disciple], <JESUS>he
        must deny himself</JESUS> [set aside selfish interests], <JESUS>and </JESUS><JESUS>take
        up his cross</JESUS> [expressing a willingness to endure whatever may come]
        <JESUS>and follow Me</JESUS> [believing in Me, conforming to My example in
        living and, if need be, suffering or perhaps dying because of faith in Me]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>For whoever wishes to save his life</JESUS> [in this world]
        <JESUS>will</JESUS> [eventually] <JESUS>lose it</JESUS> [through death],
        <JESUS>but whoever loses his life</JESUS> [in this world] <JESUS>for My sake
        and the gospel\u2019s will save it</JESUS> [from the consequences of sin
        and separation from God]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>For what does it benefit a man to gain the whole world</JESUS>
        [with all its pleasures], <JESUS>and forfeit his soul?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>For what will a man give in exchange for his soul </JESUS>and
        eternal life [in God\u2019s kingdom]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>For whoever is ashamed</JESUS> [here and now] <JESUS>of Me
        and My words in this adulterous and sinful generation, the Son of Man will
        also be ashamed of him when He comes in the glory of His Father with the
        holy angels.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Transfiguration'
      title: The Transfiguration
      number: 1
      content: "  And Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most
        solemnly say to you, there are <JESUS>some of those who are standing here
        who will not taste (experience) death before they see the kingdom of God
        after it has come with power.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Six days later, Jesus took with Him Peter and James and John, and
        led them up on a high mountain by themselves. And He was transfigured (changed
        in form) before them [and began to shine brightly with divine and regal glory]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and His clothes became radiant and dazzling, intensely white, as
        no launderer on earth can whiten them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Elijah appeared to them along with Moses, and they were having a
        conversation with Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Peter responded and said to Jesus, \u201CRabbi (Master), it is good
        for us to be here; let us make three [sacred] tents\u2014one for You, and
        one for Moses, and one for Elijah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For he did not [really] know what to say because they were terrified
        [and stunned by the miraculous sight]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then a cloud formed, overshadowing them, and a voice came out of
        the cloud, \u201CThis is My beloved Son. Listen to Him and obey Him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Suddenly they looked around and no longer saw anyone with them, except
        Jesus alone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'As they were coming down from the mountain, Jesus expressly ordered
        them not to tell anyone what they had seen, until the Son of Man had risen
        from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So they [carefully and faithfully] kept the matter to themselves,
        discussing and questioning [with one another] what it meant to rise from
        the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "They asked Him, saying, \u201CWhy do the scribes say that Elijah
        must come first [before the Messiah comes]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He answered them, <JESUS>\u201CElijah does come first and restores
        </JESUS>and reestablishes all things. And yet how is it written of the Son
        of Man that He will suffer many things [grief and physical distress] <JESUS>and
        be treated with contempt</JESUS> [utterly despised and rejected]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: All Things Possible'
      title: All Things Possible
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>But I say to you that Elijah has in fact come</JESUS> [already],
        <JESUS>and they </JESUS><JESUS>did to him whatever they wished, just as it
        is written</JESUS> [in Scripture] <JESUS>of him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When they came [back] to the [other nine] disciples, they saw a large
        crowd around them, and scribes questioning and arguing with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Immediately, when the entire crowd saw Jesus, they were startled
        and began running up to greet Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He asked them, <JESUS>\u201CWhat are you discussing with them?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "One of the crowd replied to Him, \u201CTeacher, I brought You my
        son, possessed with a spirit which makes him unable to speak; "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and whenever it seizes him [intending to do harm], it throws him
        down, and he foams [at the mouth], and grinds his teeth and becomes stiff.
        I told Your disciples to drive it out, and they could not do it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He replied, <JESUS>\u201CO unbelieving (faithless) generation, how
        long shall I be with you? How long shall I put up with you? Bring him to
        Me!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They brought the boy to Him. When the [demonic] spirit saw Him, immediately
        it threw the boy into a convulsion, and falling to the ground he began rolling
        around and foaming at the mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Jesus asked his father, <JESUS>\u201CHow long has this been happening
        to him?\u201D</JESUS> And he answered, \u201CSince childhood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The demon has often thrown him both into fire and into water, intending
        to kill him. But if You can do anything, take pity on us and help us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus said to him, \u201C[You say to Me,] <JESUS>\u2018If You can?\u2019
        All things are possible for the one who believes </JESUS>and trusts [in Me]!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Immediately the father of the boy cried out [with a desperate, piercing
        cry], saying, \u201CI do believe; help [me overcome] my unbelief.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "When Jesus saw that a crowd was rapidly gathering [around them],
        He rebuked the unclean spirit, saying to it, <JESUS>\u201CYou deaf and mute
        spirit, I command you, come out of him and never enter him again!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "After screaming out and throwing him into a terrible convulsion,
        it came out. The boy looked so much like a corpse [so still and pale] that
        many [of the spectators] said, \u201CHe is dead!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But Jesus took him by the hand and raised him; and he stood up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "When He had gone indoors, His disciples began asking Him privately,
        \u201CWhy were we unable to drive it out?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Death and Resurrection Foretold'
      title: Death and Resurrection Foretold
      number: 29
      content: "He replied to them, <JESUS>\u201CThis kind</JESUS> [of unclean spirit]
        <JESUS>cannot come out by anything but prayer</JESUS> [to the Father].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'They went on from there and began to go through Galilee. Jesus did
        not want anyone to know it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "because He was teaching His disciples [and preparing them for the
        future]. He told them, <JESUS>\u201CThe Son of Man is to be betrayed </JESUS>and
        handed over to men [who are His enemies], <JESUS>and they will kill Him;
        and when He has been killed, He will rise</JESUS> [from the dead] <JESUS>three
        days later.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'But they did not understand this statement, and they were afraid
        to ask Him [what He meant].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "They arrived at Capernaum; and when He was in the house, He asked
        them, <JESUS>\u201CWhat were you discussing </JESUS>and arguing about on
        the road?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But they kept quiet, because on the road they had discussed and debated
        with one another which one [of them] was the greatest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Sitting down [to teach], He called the twelve [disciples] and said
        to them, <JESUS>\u201CIf anyone wants to be first, he must be last of all</JESUS>
        [in importance] <JESUS>and a servant of all.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Taking a child, He set him before them; and taking him in His arms,
        He said to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Dire Warnings'
      title: Dire Warnings
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhoever receives </JESUS>and welcomes one child such
        as this in My name receives Me; and whoever receives Me receives not [only]
        <JESUS>Me, but Him who sent Me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "John said to Him, \u201CTeacher, we saw someone casting out demons
        in Your name, and we tried to stop him because he was not accompanying us
        [as Your disciple].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CDo not stop him; for there is no one
        who will perform a miracle in My name, and be able soon afterward to speak
        evil of Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: '<JESUS>For he who is not against us is for us.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '<JESUS>For whoever gives you a cup of water to drink because of your
        name as followers of Christ, I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to
        you, he will not lose his reward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut whoever causes one of these little ones who believe
        </JESUS>and trust in Me to stumble [that is, to sin or lose faith], <JESUS>it
        would be better for him if a heavy millstone</JESUS> [one requiring a donkey\u2019s
        strength to turn it] <JESUS>were hung around his neck and he were thrown
        into the sea.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '<JESUS>If your hand causes you to stumble </JESUS>and sin, cut it
        off [that is, remove yourself from the source of temptation]! <JESUS>It is
        better for you to enter life crippled, than to have two hands and go into
        </JESUS><JESUS>hell, into the unquenchable fire,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '<JESUS>[</JESUS>where their worm does not die, and the fire is not
        put out.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: '<JESUS>If your foot causes you to stumble </JESUS>and sin, cut it
        off [that is, remove yourself from the source of temptation]! <JESUS>It would
        be better for you to enter life lame than to have two feet and be thrown
        into hell,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>[</JESUS>where their worm does not die, and the fire is not
        put out.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '<JESUS>If your eye causes you to stumble </JESUS>and sin, throw it
        out [that is, remove yourself from the source of temptation]! <JESUS>It would
        be better for you to enter the kingdom of God with one eye, than to have
        two eyes and be thrown into hell,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '<JESUS>where </JESUS>their worm [that feeds on the dead] <JESUS>does
        not die</JESUS>, and the fire is not put out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CFor everyone will be salted with fire.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "<JESUS>Salt is good </JESUS>and useful; but if salt has lost its
        saltiness (purpose), how will you make it salty? Have salt within yourselves
        continually, and be at peace with one another.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jesus\u2019 Teaching about Divorce"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Teaching about Divorce"
      number: 1
      content: '  Getting up, He left there (Capernaum) and went to the region of
        Judea and beyond the Jordan; and crowds gathered around Him again and accompanied
        Him, and as was His custom, He once more began to teach them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Pharisees came to Jesus to test Him [intending to trick Him into
        saying something wrong], and asked Him, \u201CIs it lawful [according to
        Scripture] for a man to divorce his wife and send her away?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He replied to them, <JESUS>\u201CWhat did Moses command you?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They said, \u201CMoses allowed a man  to write a certificate of divorce
        and to send her away.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CBecause of your hardness of
        hearts</JESUS> [your callousness and insensitivity toward your wives and
        the provision of God] <JESUS>he wrote you this precept.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>But from the beginning of creation </JESUS>God  made them
        male and female.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>F</JESUS>or this reason a man shall leave his father and his
        mother [to establish a home with his wife], '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>and the two shall become one flesh</JESUS>; so that they are
        no longer two, but [are united as] <JESUS>one flesh.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>Therefore, what God has united </JESUS>and joined together,
        man must not separate [by divorce].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In the house the disciples began questioning Him again about this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CWhoever divorces his wife and marries
        another woman commits adultery against her;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Jesus Blesses Little Children'
      title: Jesus Blesses Little Children
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>and if a woman divorces her husband and marries another man,
        she commits adultery.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'People were bringing children to Him so that He would touch and bless
        them, but the disciples reprimanded them and discouraged them [from coming]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But when Jesus saw this, He was indignant and He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CAllow
        the children to come to Me; do not forbid them; for the kingdom of God belongs
        to such as these.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, whoever
        does not receive and welcome the kingdom of God like a child will not enter
        it at all.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Rich Young Ruler'
      title: The Rich Young Ruler
      number: 16
      content: 'And He took the children [one by one] in His arms and blessed them
        [with kind, encouraging words], placing His hands on them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "As He was leaving on His journey, a man ran up and knelt before Him
        and asked Him, \u201CGood Teacher [You who are essentially good and morally
        perfect], what shall I do to inherit eternal life [that is, eternal salvation
        in the Messiah\u2019s kingdom]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>Why do you call Me
        good? No one is</JESUS> [essentially] <JESUS>good</JESUS> [by nature] <JESUS>except
        God alone.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>You know the commandments: \u2018D</JESUS>o not murder, Do
        not commit adultery, Do not steal, Do not testify falsely, Do not defraud,
        Honor your father and mother.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he replied to Him, \u201CTeacher, I have [carefully] kept all
        these [commandments] since my youth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Looking at him, Jesus felt a love (high regard, compassion) for him,
        and He said to him, <JESUS>\u201CYou lack one thing: go and sell all your
        property and give</JESUS> [the money] <JESUS>to the poor, and you will have</JESUS>
        [abundant] <JESUS>treasure in heaven; and come, follow Me</JESUS> [becoming
        My disciple, believing and trusting in Me and walking the same path of life
        that I walk].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But the man was saddened at Jesus\u2019 words, and he left grieving,
        because he owned much property and had many possessions [which he treasured
        more than his relationship with God].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus looked around and said to His disciples, <JESUS>\u201CHow difficult
        it will be for those who are wealthy</JESUS> [and cling to possessions and
        status as security] <JESUS>to enter the kingdom of God!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The disciples were amazed and bewildered by His words. But Jesus
        said to them again, <JESUS>\u201CChildren, how difficult it is</JESUS> [for
        those who place their hope and confidence in riches] <JESUS>to enter the
        kingdom of God!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle
        than for a rich man</JESUS> [who places his faith in wealth or status] <JESUS>to
        enter the kingdom of God.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "They were completely and utterly astonished, and said to Him, \u201CThen
        who can be saved [from the wrath of God]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Looking at them, Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CWith people</JESUS> [as
        far as it depends on them] <JESUS>it is impossible, but not with God; for
        all things are possible with God.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Peter started saying to Him, \u201CLook, we have given up everything
        and followed You [becoming Your disciples and accepting You as Teacher and
        Lord].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say
        to you, there is no one who has given up a house or brothers or sisters or
        mother or father or children or farms, for My sake and for the gospel\u2019s
        sake,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>who will not receive a hundred times as much now in the present
        age\u2014houses and brothers and sisters and mothers and children and farms\u2014along
        with persecutions; and in the age to come, eternal life.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: "31: Jesus\u2019 Sufferings Foretold"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Sufferings Foretold"
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>But many </JESUS>who are first will be last, and the last,
        first.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now they were on the road going up to Jerusalem, and Jesus was walking
        on ahead of them; and they were perplexed [at what Jesus had said], and those
        who were following were alarmed and afraid. And again He took the twelve
        [disciples] aside and began telling them what was going to happen to Him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "saying, <JESUS>\u201CListen very carefully: we are going up to Jerusalem,
        and the Son of Man will be betrayed </JESUS>and handed over to the chief
        priests and the scribes; and they will condemn Him to death and hand Him
        over to the Gentiles (Romans).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>They will mock </JESUS>and ridicule Him and spit on Him, and
        whip (scourge) Him and kill Him, and three days later He will rise [from
        the dead].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "James and John, the two sons of Zebedee, came to Him, saying, \u201CTeacher,
        we want You to do for us whatever we ask of You.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And He replied to them, <JESUS>\u201CWhat do you want Me to do for
        you?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "They said to Him, \u201CGrant that we may sit [with You], one on
        Your right and one on Your left, in Your glory [Your majesty and splendor
        in Your kingdom].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CYou do not know what you are
        asking. Are you able to drink the cup that I drink, or to be baptized with
        the baptism</JESUS> [of suffering and death] <JESUS>with which I am baptized?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And they replied to Him, \u201CWe are able.\u201D Jesus told them,
        <JESUS>\u201CThe cup that I drink you will drink, and you will be baptized
        with the baptism with which I am baptized.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "<JESUS>But to sit on My right or left, this is not Mine to give;
        but it is for those for whom it has been prepared</JESUS> [by My Father].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Hearing this, the [other] ten became indignant with James and John. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Calling them to Himself, Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CYou know
        that those who are recognized as rulers of the Gentiles lord it over them;
        and their powerful men exercise authority over them</JESUS> [tyrannizing
        them]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '<JESUS>But this is not how it is among you; instead, whoever wishes
        to become great among you must be your servant,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '<JESUS>and whoever wishes to be first </JESUS>and most important
        among you must be slave of all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: Bartimaeus Receives His Sight'
      title: Bartimaeus Receives His Sight
      number: 45
      content: "<JESUS>For even the Son of Man did not come to be served, but to
        serve, and to give His life as a </JESUS><JESUS>ransom for many.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Then they came to Jericho. And as He was leaving Jericho with His
        disciples and a large crowd, a blind beggar, Bartimaeus, the son of Timaeus,
        was sitting beside the road [as was his custom]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "When Bartimaeus heard that it was Jesus of Nazareth, he began to
        shout and say, \u201CJesus, Son of David (Messiah), have mercy on me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Many sternly rebuked him, telling him to keep still and be quiet;
        but he kept on shouting out all the more, \u201CSon of David (Messiah), have
        mercy on me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Jesus stopped and said, <JESUS>\u201CCall him.\u201D</JESUS> So they
        called the blind man, telling him, \u201CTake courage, get up! He is calling
        for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Throwing his cloak aside, he jumped up and came to Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "And Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CWhat do you want Me to do for you?\u201D</JESUS>
        The blind man said to Him, \u201CRabboni (my Master), let me regain my sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CGo; your faith</JESUS> [and confident
        trust in My power] <JESUS>has made you well.\u201D</JESUS> Immediately he
        regained his sight and began following Jesus on the road."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Triumphal Entry'
      title: The Triumphal Entry
      number: 1
      content: '  When they were nearing Jerusalem, at Bethphage and Bethany near
        the Mount of Olives, Jesus sent two of His disciples, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "saying to them, <JESUS>\u201CGo into the </JESUS><JESUS>village in
        front of you, and immediately as you enter it, you will find a</JESUS> [donkey\u2019s]
        <JESUS>colt tied, which has never been ridden by anyone; untie it and bring
        it here.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>If anyone asks you, \u2018Why are you doing this?\u2019 say,
        \u2018The Lord needs it\u2019; and immediately he will send it here.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So they went away [to the village] and found a colt tied outside
        at a gate in the street, and they untied it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Some of the people who were standing there said to them, \u201CWhat
        are you doing, untying the colt?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They replied to them just as Jesus had directed, and they allowed
        them to go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They brought the colt to Jesus and put their coats on it, and He
        sat on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And many [of the people] spread their coats on the road [as an act
        of tribute and homage before a new king], and others [scattered a layer of]
        leafy branches which they had cut from the fields [honoring Him as Messiah]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Those who went in front and those who were following [Him] were shouting
        [in joy and praise],\u201CHosanna (Save, I pray)!Blessed (praised, glorified)
        is He who comes in the name of the Lord!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Blessed is the coming kingdom of our father David!Hosanna in the
        highest [heaven]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Jesus entered Jerusalem and went to the temple [enclosure]; and after
        looking around at everything, He left for Bethany with the twelve [disciples],
        because it was already late [in the day].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On the next day, when they had left Bethany, He was hungry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Seeing at a distance a fig tree in leaf, He went to see if He would
        find anything on it. But He found nothing but leaves, for it was not the
        season for figs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Jesus Drives Moneychangers from the Temple'
      title: Jesus Drives Moneychangers from the Temple
      number: 14
      content: "He said to it, <JESUS>\u201CNo one will ever eat fruit from you again!\u201D</JESUS>
        And His disciples were listening [to what He said].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then they came to Jerusalem. And He entered the temple [grounds]
        and began driving out [with force] the people who were selling and buying
        [animals for sacrifice] in the temple area, and overturned the tables of
        the moneychangers [who made a profit exchanging foreign money for temple
        coinage] and the seats of those who were selling doves; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and He would not permit anyone to carry merchandise or household
        wares through the temple [grounds, using the temple area irreverently as
        a shortcut]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He began to teach and say to them, <JESUS>\u201CIs it not written,
        \u2018M</JESUS>y house shall be called a house of prayer for all the nations\u2019?
        But you have made it a robbers\u2019 den.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The chief priests and the scribes heard this and began searching
        for a way to destroy Him; for they were afraid of Him, since the entire crowd
        was struck with astonishment at His teaching.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When evening came, Jesus and His disciples would leave the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In the morning, as they were passing by, the disciples saw that the
        fig tree had withered away from the roots up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And remembering, Peter said to Him, \u201CRabbi (Master), look! The
        fig tree which You cursed has withered!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CHave faith in God</JESUS> [constantly]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, whoever
        says to this mountain, \u2018Be lifted up and thrown into the sea!\u2019
        and <JESUS>does not doubt in his heart</JESUS> [in God\u2019s unlimited power],
        <JESUS>but believes that what he says is going to take place, it will be
        done for him</JESUS> [in accordance with God\u2019s will]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>For this reason I am telling you, whatever things you ask
        for in prayer</JESUS> [in accordance with God\u2019s will], <JESUS>believe</JESUS>
        [with confident trust] <JESUS>that you have received them, and they will
        be </JESUS>given to you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>Whenever you </JESUS><JESUS>stand praying, if you have anything
        against anyone, forgive him</JESUS> [drop the issue, let it go], <JESUS>so
        that your Father who is in heaven will also forgive you your transgressions
        </JESUS>and wrongdoings [against Him and others]. '
      comments: []
    - name: "26: Jesus\u2019 Authority Questioned"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Authority Questioned"
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>[</JESUS>But if you do not forgive, neither will your Father
        in heaven forgive your transgressions.\u201D]  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They came again to Jerusalem. And as Jesus was walking in the [courts
        and porches of the] temple, the chief priests, the scribes, and the elders
        came to Him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "and began saying to Him, \u201CBy what authority are You doing these
        things, or who gave You this authority to do these things?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CI will ask you one question, and
        you answer Me, and then I will tell you by what authority I do these things.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>Was the baptism of John</JESUS> [the Baptist] <JESUS>from
        heaven</JESUS> [that is, ordained by God] <JESUS>or from men? Answer Me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "They began discussing it with each other, saying, \u201CIf we say,
        \u2018From heaven,\u2019 He will say, \u2018Then why did you not believe
        him?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But shall we say, \u2018From men?\u2019\u2009\u201D \u2014they were
        afraid [to answer because] of the crowd, for everyone considered John to
        have been a real prophet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So they replied to Jesus, \u201CWe do not know.\u201D And Jesus said
        to them, <JESUS>\u201CNeither will I tell you by what authority I do these
        things.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Parable of the Vineyard Owner'
      title: Parable of the Vineyard Owner
      number: 1
      content: "  Jesus began to speak to them [the chief priests, scribes and elders
        who were questioning Him] in parables: <JESUS>\u201CA man </JESUS>planted
        a vineyard and put a  <JESUS>wall around it</JESUS>, and dug a pit for the
        wine press and built a tower; and he rented it out to tenant farmers and
        left the country.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>When the </JESUS>harvest season came he sent a <JESUS>servant
        to the tenants, in order to collect from them some of the fruit of the vineyard.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>They took him and beat him and sent him away empty-handed.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>Again he sent them another servant, and they</JESUS> [threw
        stones and] <JESUS>wounded him in the head, and treated him disgracefully.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>And he sent another, and that one they killed; then many others\u2014some
        they beat and some they killed.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>He still had one man left </JESUS>to send, a beloved son;
        he sent him last of all to them, saying, \u2018They will respect my son.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>But those tenants said to each other, \u2018This </JESUS>man
        is the heir! Come on, let us kill him [and destroy the evidence], <JESUS>and
        his inheritance will be ours!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>So they took him and killed him, and threw his body outside
        the vineyard.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<JESUS>What will the owner of the vineyard do? He will come and destroy
        the tenants, and will give the vineyard to others.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>Have you not even read this Scripture:</JESUS>  <JESUS>\u2018T</JESUS>he
        stone which the builders regarded as unworthy  and  rejected,  <JESUS>T</JESUS>his
        [very stone] <JESUS>has become the chief</JESUS> Cornerstone  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  <JESUS>T</JESUS>his came about from the Lord,  <JESUS>A</JESUS>nd
        it is marvelous  and  wonderful in our eyes\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Jesus Answers the Pharisees, Sadducees and Scribes'
      title: Jesus Answers the Pharisees, Sadducees and Scribes
      number: 12
      content: 'And they were looking for a way to seize Him, but they were afraid
        of the crowd; for they knew that He spoke this parable in reference to [and
        as a charge against] them. And so they left Him and went away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they sent some of the Pharisees and Herodians to Jesus in order
        to trap Him into making a statement [that they could use against Him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They came and said to Him, \u201CTeacher, we know that You are truthful
        and have no personal bias toward anyone; for You are not influenced by outward
        appearances or social status, but in truth You teach the way of God. Is it
        lawful [according to Jewish law and tradition] to pay the poll-tax to [Tiberius]
        Caesar, or not? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Should we pay [the tax] or should we not pay?\u201D But knowing their
        hypocrisy, He asked them, <JESUS>\u201CWhy are you testing Me? Bring Me a
        </JESUS><JESUS>coin (denarius) to look at.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So they brought one. Then He asked them, <JESUS>\u201CWhose image
        and inscription is this?\u201D</JESUS> They said to Him, \u201CCaesar\u2019s.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CPay to Caesar the things that are
        Caesar\u2019s, and to God the things that are God\u2019s.\u201D</JESUS> And
        they were greatly amazed at Him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Some Sadducees (who say that there is no resurrection) came to Him,
        and began questioning Him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CTeacher, Moses wrote for us [a law] that if a man\u2019s brother
        dies and leaves a wife but leaves no child, his brother is to  marry the
        widow and raise up children for his brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'There were seven brothers; the first [one] took a wife, and died
        leaving no children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The second brother married her, and died leaving no children; and
        the third likewise; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and so all seven [married her and died, and] left no children. Last
        of all the woman died also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "In the resurrection, whose wife will she be? For all seven [brothers]
        were married to her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CIs this not why you are wrong, because
        you know neither the Scriptures</JESUS> [that teach the resurrection] <JESUS>nor
        the power of God</JESUS> [who is able to raise the dead]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>For when they rise from the dead, they do not marry nor are
        they given in marriage, but are like angels in heaven.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>But concerning the raising of the dead, have you not read
        in the book of Moses, in the </JESUS>passage about the burning bush, how
        God spoke to him, saying, \u2018I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac,
        and the God of Jacob\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>He is not the God of the dead, but of the living; you are
        greatly mistaken </JESUS>and you are deceiving yourselves!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then one of the scribes [an expert in Mosaic Law] came up and listened
        to them arguing [with one another], and noticing that Jesus answered them
        well, asked Him, \u201CWhich commandment is first and most important of all?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CThe first </JESUS>and most important
        one is: \u2018Hear, O Israel, the Lord our God is one Lord;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>and you shall love the</JESUS> Lord your God with all your
        heart, and with all your soul (life), and with all your mind (thought, understanding),
        and with all your strength.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>This is the second: \u2018Y</JESUS>ou shall [unselfishly]
        <JESUS>love your neighbor as yourself</JESUS>.\u2019 There is no other commandment
        greater than these.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The scribe said to Him, \u201CAdmirably answered, Teacher; You truthfully
        stated that He is One, and there is no other but Him; "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "and to love Him with all the heart and with all the understanding
        and with all the strength, and to [unselfishly] love one\u2019s neighbor
        as oneself, is much more than all burnt offerings and sacrifices.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "When Jesus saw that he answered thoughtfully and intelligently, He
        said to him, <JESUS>\u201CYou are not far from the kingdom of God.\u201D</JESUS>
        And after that, no one would dare to ask Him any more questions.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jesus began to say, as He taught in [a portico or court of] the temple,
        <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>How can the scribes say that the Christ is the
        son of David?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>David himself said</JESUS> [when inspired] <JESUS>by the Holy
        Spirit,</JESUS>  <JESUS>\u2018T</JESUS>he Lord (the Father) said to my Lord
        (the Son, the Messiah),  <JESUS>\u201CS</JESUS>it at My right hand,  <JESUS>U</JESUS>ntil
        I put Your enemies under Your feet.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "  <JESUS>David himself calls Him (the Son, the Messiah) \u2018Lord\u2019;
        so how can it be that He is </JESUS>    <JESUS>David\u2019s Son?\u201D</JESUS>
        The large crowd enjoyed hearing Jesus and listened to Him with delight.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "In [the course of] His teaching He was saying, <JESUS>\u201CBeware
        of the scribes, who like to walk around in long robes</JESUS> [displaying
        their prominence], <JESUS>and </JESUS>like to receive respectful greetings
        in the market places,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '<JESUS>and</JESUS> [they love] <JESUS>the </JESUS><JESUS>chief seats
        in the synagogues and the places of distinction </JESUS>and honor at banquets,  '
      comments: []
    - name: "40: The Widow\u2019s Mite"
      title: "The Widow\u2019s Mite"
      number: 40
      content: "[these scribes] <JESUS>who devour (confiscate) widows\u2019 houses,
        and offer long prayers for appearance\u2019s sake</JESUS> [to impress others].
        <JESUS>These men will receive greater condemnation.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And He sat down opposite the [temple] treasury, and began watching
        how the people were putting money into the treasury. And many rich people
        were putting in large sums. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'A poor widow came and put in two small copper coins, which amount
        to a mite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Calling His disciples to Him, He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CI assure
        you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, this poor widow put in [proportionally]
        <JESUS>more than all the contributors to the treasury.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "<JESUS>For they all contributed from their surplus, but she, from
        her poverty, put in all she had, all she had to live on.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Things to Come'
      title: Things to Come
      number: 1
      content: "  As He was coming out of the temple [grounds], one of His disciples
        said to Him, \u201CTeacher, look what wonderful stones and what wonderful
        buildings!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Jesus replied to him, <JESUS>\u201CYou see these great buildings?
        Not one stone will be left on another which will not be </JESUS><JESUS>torn
        down!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As He was sitting on the Mount of Olives opposite the temple, Peter
        and James and John and Andrew asked Him privately, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTell us, when will these things happen, and what will be the
        sign when all these things are about to be fulfilled?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jesus began to say to them, <JESUS>\u201CBe careful </JESUS>and see
        to it that no one misleads you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>Many will come in My name</JESUS> [misusing My name or claiming
        to be the Messiah], <JESUS>saying, \u2018I am </JESUS>He!\u2019 and will
        deceive and mislead many.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>When you hear of wars and rumors of wars, do not be alarmed
        (frightened, troubled); </JESUS>these things must take place, but the end
        is not yet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>For nation will rise up against nation, and kingdom against
        kingdom; there will be earthquakes in various places; there will be famines.
        These things are the beginning of the </JESUS><JESUS>birth pangs</JESUS>
        [the intolerable anguish and suffering].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut be on your guard; they will turn you over to courts,
        and you will be beaten in synagogues, and you will stand</JESUS> [as accused]
        <JESUS>before governors and kings for My sake, as a testimony to them.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>The gospel</JESUS> [that is, the good news regarding the way
        of salvation] <JESUS>must first be preached to all the</JESUS> [Gentile]
        <JESUS>nations.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>When they take you and turn you over</JESUS> [to the court],
        <JESUS>do not worry beforehand about what to say, but say whatever is given
        to you</JESUS> [by God] <JESUS>in that hour; for it is not you who speak,
        but it is the Holy Spirit</JESUS> [who will speak through you]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>Brother will betray brother to</JESUS> [be put to] <JESUS>death,
        and a father</JESUS> [will hand over] <JESUS>his child; and children will
        rise up </JESUS>and take a stand against parents and have them put to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>You will be hated by everyone because of</JESUS> [your association
        with] <JESUS>My name, but the one who</JESUS> [patiently perseveres empowered
        by the Holy Spirit and] <JESUS>endures to the end, he will be saved.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut when you see the </JESUS>    <JESUS>  </JESUS>abomination
        of desolation standing [in the temple sanctuary] <JESUS>where it ought not
        to be </JESUS>(let the reader understand) then those who are in Judea must
        flee to the mountains. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>Whoever is on the housetop must not go down</JESUS> [to enter
        the house], <JESUS>or go inside to take anything out of his house;</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>whoever is in the field must not turn back to get his coat.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>And woe to those women who are pregnant and to those who are
        nursing babies in those days!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>Pray that it will not occur in winter,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>for at that time there will be such tribulation as has not
        occurred, from the beginning of the creation which God made, until now\u2014and
        never will</JESUS> [be again]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>And if the Lord had not shortened the days, no human life
        would have been saved; but for the sake of the elect, whom He chose</JESUS>
        [for Himself], <JESUS>He shortened the days.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>Then if anyone says to you, \u2018Look, here is the Christ
        (the Messiah, the Anointed)!\u2019 or, \u2018Look, </JESUS>He is there!\u2019
        do not believe it;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>for false Christs and false prophets will arise, and they
        will provide signs and wonders in order to deceive, if</JESUS> [such a thing
        were] <JESUS>possible, even the elect</JESUS> [those God has chosen for Himself]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The Return of Christ'
      title: The Return of Christ
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>But be on your guard; I have told you everything in advance.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut in those days, after</JESUS> [the suffering and
        distress of] <JESUS>that tribulation, </JESUS>the sun will be darkened, and
        the moon will not give its light,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>and the stars will be falling</JESUS> from the sky, and the
        powers that are in the heavens will be shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>Then they will see </JESUS>the Son of Man coming in clouds
        with great power and glory [in royal majesty and splendor]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>And then He will send out the angels, and will gather together
        His elect</JESUS> [those He has chosen for Himself] <JESUS>from the four
        winds, from the farthest end of the earth to the farthest end of heaven.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNow learn this lesson from the fig tree: as soon as
        its branch becomes tender and it puts out its leaves, you recognize that
        summer is near.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>Even so, you too, when you see these things happening, know</JESUS>
        [for certain] <JESUS>that He is near, </JESUS>right at the door.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, this generation
        [the people living when these signs and events begin] <JESUS>will not pass
        away until all these things take place.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '<JESUS>Heaven and earth</JESUS> [as now known] <JESUS>will </JESUS><JESUS>pass
        away, but My words will not pass away.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>But of that</JESUS> [exact] <JESUS>day or hour no one knows,
        not even the angels in heaven, nor the Son</JESUS> [in His humanity], <JESUS>but
        the Father </JESUS>alone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBe on guard and stay constantly alert </JESUS>   
        <JESUS>  </JESUS>[and pray]; for you do not know when the appointed time
        will come.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>It is like a man away on a journey, </JESUS>who when he left
        home put his servants in charge, each with his particular task, and also
        ordered the doorkeeper to be continually alert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>Therefore, be </JESUS>continually on the alert\u2014for you
        do not know when the master of the house is coming, whether in the evening,
        or at midnight, or when the rooster crows, or in the morning\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '[stay alert,] <JESUS>in case he should come suddenly </JESUS>and
        unexpectedly and find you asleep and unprepared.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>What I say to you I say to everyone, \u2018Be on the alert</JESUS>
        [stay awake and be continually cautious]!\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Death Plot and the Anointing in Bethany'
      title: Death Plot and the Anointing in Bethany
      number: 1
      content: '  It was now two days before the Passover and [the festival of] Unleavened
        Bread, and the chief priests and the scribes were searching for a deceitful
        way to arrest Jesus and kill Him;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "but they were saying, \u201CNot during the festival, for the people
        might riot.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'While He was in Bethany [as a guest] at the home of Simon the leper,
        and reclining at the table, a woman came with an alabaster vial of very costly
        and precious perfume of pure nard; and she broke the vial and poured the
        perfume over His head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But there were some who were indignantly remarking to one another,
        \u201CWhy has this perfume been wasted? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For this perfume might have been sold for more than three hundred
        denarii [a laborer\u2019s wages for almost a year], and the money given to
        the poor.\u201D And they scolded her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CLet her alone; why are you bothering
        her </JESUS>and causing trouble? She has done a good and beautiful thing
        to Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>For you always have the poor with you, and whenever you wish
        you can do something good to them; but you will not always have Me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>She has done what she could; she has anointed My body beforehand
        for the burial.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, wherever
        the good news [regarding salvation] <JESUS>is proclaimed throughout the world,
        what she has done will be told in memory of her.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Judas Iscariot, who was one of the twelve [disciples], went
        to the chief priests to betray Jesus to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Last Passover'
      title: The Last Passover
      number: 11
      content: 'When they heard this they were delighted, and promised to give him
        money. And he began looking for an opportune time to betray Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "On the first day [of the festival] of Unleavened Bread, when [as
        was customary] they sacrificed the Passover lamb, His disciples asked Him,
        \u201CWhere do You want us to go and prepare for You to eat the Passover?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And He sent two of His disciples, saying to them, <JESUS>\u201CGo
        into the city, and a </JESUS><JESUS>man carrying a jar of water will meet
        you; follow him;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>and say to the </JESUS><JESUS>owner of the </JESUS>house he
        enters, \u2018The Teacher asks, \u201CWhere is My guest room in which I may
        eat the Passover with My disciples?\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>He will show you a large upstairs room, furnished and ready</JESUS>
        [with carpets and dining couches]; <JESUS>prepare</JESUS> [the supper] <JESUS>for
        us there.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The disciples left and went to the city and found everything just
        as He had told them, and they prepared the Passover.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When it was evening, He came with the twelve [disciples]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "While they were reclining at the table, Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI
        assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you that one of you will betray
        Me\u2014one who is eating with Me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They began to be grieved and deeply distressed and to say to Him
        one by one, \u201CSurely not I?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And He replied, <JESUS>\u201CIt is one of the twelve</JESUS> [disciples],
        <JESUS>one who is dipping </JESUS>bread in the bowl with Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "21: The Lord\u2019s Supper"
      title: "The Lord\u2019s Supper"
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>For the Son of Man goes</JESUS> [to the cross] <JESUS>just
        as it is written</JESUS> [in Scripture] <JESUS>of Him; but woe to that man
        by whom the Son of Man is betrayed! </JESUS>It would have been good for that
        man if he had not been born.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "While they were eating, Jesus took bread and blessed it [giving thanks
        and praise], and He broke it, and gave it to them and said, <JESUS>\u201CTake
        it. This is My body.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And when He had taken a cup [of wine] and given thanks, He gave it
        to them, and they all drank from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CThis is My blood of the</JESUS>
        [new] <JESUS>covenant,</JESUS> [My blood] <JESUS>which is being poured out
        for many</JESUS> [for the forgiveness of sins]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, I will
        not drink again of the fruit of the vine until that day when I drink it new
        in the kingdom of God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'After they had sung a hymn, they went out to the Mount of Olives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CYou will all fall away</JESUS> [and
        be ashamed and be afraid to be associated with Me as disciples], <JESUS>because
        it is written, \u2018I </JESUS>will strike the Shepherd, and the sheep will
        be scattered.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>But after I have been raised</JESUS> [from the dead], <JESUS>I
        will go ahead of you to Galilee.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But Peter said to Him, \u201CEven if they all fall away [and desert
        You, ashamed and afraid of being associated with You], yet I will not [do
        so]!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly
        say to you, this very night, before a rooster crows twice, you will deny
        [that you even know] <JESUS>Me three times.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Jesus in Gethsemane'
      title: Jesus in Gethsemane
      number: 31
      content: "But Peter kept saying insistently, \u201CIf I have to die with You,
        I will not deny You!\u201D And they all were saying the same thing as well.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then they went to a place called Gethsemane; and Jesus said to His
        disciples, <JESUS>\u201CSit down here until I have prayed.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He took Peter and James and John with Him, and He began to be deeply
        distressed and troubled [extremely anguished at the prospect of what was
        to come]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CMy soul is deeply grieved </JESUS>and
        overwhelmed with sorrow, to the point of death; remain here and keep watch.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "After going a little farther, He fell to the ground [distressed by
        the weight of His spiritual burden] and began to pray that if it were possible
        [in the Father\u2019s will], the hour [of suffering and death for the sins
        of mankind] might pass from Him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "He was saying, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>Abba, Father! All things
        are possible for You; take this cup</JESUS> [of judgment] <JESUS>away from
        Me; but not what I will, but what You will.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And He came back and found them sleeping, and He said to Peter, <JESUS>\u201CSimon,
        are you asleep? Were you unable to keep watch for one hour?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>Keep</JESUS> [actively] <JESUS>watching and praying so that
        you do not come into temptation; the spirit is willing, but the </JESUS><JESUS>body
        is weak.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'He went away again and prayed, saying the same words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And again He came back and found them sleeping, because their eyes
        were very heavy; and they did not know how to answer Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "He came back a third time and said to them, <JESUS>\u201CAre you
        still sleeping and resting? Enough</JESUS> [of that]! <JESUS>The hour has
        come. Look, the Son of Man is being betrayed into the hands of sinners.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: Betrayal and Arrest'
      title: Betrayal and Arrest
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>Get up, let us go. Look, my betrayer is near!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And at once, while He was still speaking, Judas [Iscariot], one of
        the twelve [disciples], came up, and with him a crowd of men with swords
        and clubs, who came from the chief priests, the scribes, and the elders [of
        the Sanhedrin]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Now the betrayer had given them a signal, saying, \u201CWhomever
        I kiss, He is the one; seize Him and lead Him away safely [under guard].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "When Judas came, immediately he went up to Jesus and said, \u201CRabbi
        (Master)!\u201D and he kissed Him [forcefully]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'They laid hands on Him and seized Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'But one of the bystanders [Simon Peter] drew his sword and struck
        [Malchus] the slave of the high priest and cut off his ear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CHave you come out with swords and
        clubs to arrest Me, as </JESUS>you would against a robber?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "<JESUS>Day after day I was with you, teaching in the</JESUS> [courts
        and porches of the] <JESUS>temple, and you did not seize Me; but </JESUS>this
        has happened so that the Scriptures would be fulfilled.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Then all of His disciples abandoned Him and fled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'A young man was following Him, wearing [only] a linen sheet over
        his naked body; and some men seized him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: Jesus before His Accusers'
      title: Jesus before His Accusers
      number: 52
      content: 'But pulling free of the linen sheet, he escaped [from them] naked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'They led Jesus away to the high priest, and all the chief priests
        and the elders and the scribes (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court) gathered together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Peter had followed Him at a distance, right into the courtyard of
        the high priest; and he was sitting with the officers [guards and servants]
        and warming himself at the fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'Now the chief priests and the entire Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High
        Court) were trying to obtain testimony against Jesus [which they could use]
        to have Him [condemned and] executed, but they were not finding any. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'For many [people] were giving false testimony against Him, but their
        testimonies were not consistent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'Some stood up and began to give false testimony against Him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "\u201CWe heard Him say, \u2018I will destroy this temple (sanctuary)
        that was made with hands, and in three days I will build another made without
        hands.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Not even in this respect was their testimony consistent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "The high priest stood up and came forward and asked Jesus, \u201CHave
        You no answer to give [in response] to what these men are testifying against
        You?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "But Jesus kept silent and gave no answer at all. Again the high priest
        was questioning Him, and saying to Him, \u201CAre You the Christ (the Messiah,
        the Anointed), the Son of the Blessed One?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI am; and you will</JESUS> [all] <JESUS>see
        </JESUS>the Son of Man seated [with authority] <JESUS>at the right hand of</JESUS>
        Power (the Father), and coming with the clouds of heaven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: "Then tearing his robe [to express his indignation], the high priest
        said, \u201CWhat further need do we have of witnesses? "
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "You have heard the blasphemy [that is, His claim to be the Son of
        God]. What is your decision?\u201D And they all condemned Him to be [guilty
        and] deserving of death. "
      comments: []
    - name: "65: Peter\u2019s Denials"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Denials"
      number: 65
      content: "And some began to spit on Him, and to blindfold Him, and to beat
        Him with their fists, and to say to Him, \u201CProphesy [by telling us who
        hit you]!\u201D Then the officers took custody of Him and struck him in the
        face.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'While Peter was down below in the courtyard, one of the servant-girls
        of the high priest came, '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "and when she saw Peter warming himself, she looked intently at him
        and said, \u201CYou were with Jesus the Nazarene, too.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: "But he denied it, saying, \u201CI neither know nor understand what
        you are talking about.\u201D Then he went out [of the courtyard] to the porch,
        [and a rooster crowed.]  "
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: "The servant-girl saw him, and began once more to tell the bystanders,
        \u201CThis [man] is one of them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: "But again he denied it. After a little while, the bystanders again
        said to Peter, \u201CYou are in fact one of them, for [it is clear from your
        accent, that] you are a Galilean, too.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: "But he began to invoke a curse [on himself] and to swear [an oath],
        \u201CI do not know this man you are talking about!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: "Immediately a rooster crowed the second time. And Peter remembered
        what Jesus said to him: <JESUS>\u201CBefore a rooster crows twice, you will
        deny Me three times.\u201D</JESUS> And thinking of this, he began weeping
        [in anguish]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus before Pilate'
      title: Jesus before Pilate
      number: 1
      content: '  Early in the morning the chief priests, with the elders and scribes
        and the whole Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court), immediately consulted
        together; and they bound Jesus, they took Him away [violently] and handed
        Him over to Pilate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Pilate questioned Him, \u201CAre You the King of the Jews?\u201D
        And He replied to him, <JESUS>\u201CIt is as you say.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The chief priests began accusing Him of many things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Pilate again asked Him, \u201CHave You no answer [to give]?
        See how many charges they are bringing against You!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But Jesus gave no further answer; so Pilate was perplexed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now at the [Passover] feast Pilate used to set free for them any
        one prisoner whom they requested. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The man called Barabbas was imprisoned with the insurrectionists
        (revolutionaries) who had committed murder in the civil rebellion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The crowd came up and began asking Pilate to do as he usually did
        for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Pilate answered them, saying, \u201CDo you want me to set free for
        you the King of the Jews?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For he was aware that the chief priests had turned Jesus over to
        him because of envy and resentment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the chief priests stirred up the crowd to get him to release
        Barabbas for them instead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Again Pilate answered, \u201CThen what shall I do with Him whom you
        call the King of the Jews?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They screamed back, \u201CCrucify Him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Pilate asked them, \u201CWhy, what has He done that is evil?\u201D
        But they screamed all the more, \u201CCrucify Him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jesus Is Mocked'
      title: Jesus Is Mocked
      number: 15
      content: 'So Pilate, wishing to satisfy the crowd, set Barabbas free for them;
        and after having Jesus scourged, he handed Him over [to his soldiers] to
        be crucified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The soldiers led Him away into the palace (that is, the Praetorium),
        and they called together the entire [Roman] battalion [of 600 soldiers]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They dressed Him up in [a ranking Roman officer\u2019s robe of] purple,
        and after twisting [together] a crown of thorns, they placed it on Him; "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and they began saluting and mocking Him: \u201CHail, King of the
        Jews!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They kept beating Him on the head with a reed and spitting on Him,
        and kneeling and bowing in [mock] homage to Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After they had mocked Him, they took off the purple robe and put
        His own clothes on Him. And they led Him out [of the city] to crucify Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Crucifixion'
      title: The Crucifixion
      number: 21
      content: 'They forced into service a passer-by coming in from the countryside,
        Simon of Cyrene (the father of Alexander and Rufus), to carry His cross.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then they brought Him to the place [called] Golgotha, which is translated,
        Place of a Skull. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They tried to give Him wine mixed with myrrh [to dull the pain],
        but He would not take it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And they crucified Him, and divided up His clothes among themselves,
        casting lots for them to see who should take what. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'It was the third hour (9:00 a.m.) when they crucified Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The inscription of the accusation against Him had been written [above
        Him]: \u201CTHE KING OF THE JEWS.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They crucified two robbers with Him, one on His right and one on
        His left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "[And the Scripture was fulfilled which says, \u201CHe was counted
        with the transgressors.\u201D]  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Those who were passing by were insulting Him with abusive and insolent
        language, wagging their heads [as a sign of contempt], and saying, \u201CHa!
        You who would destroy the temple and rebuild it in [only] three days, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "save Yourself by coming down from the cross!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "In the same way the chief priests also, along with the scribes, were
        ridiculing and mocking Him among themselves and saying, \u201CHe saved others
        [from death]; He cannot save Himself! "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Let the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed), the King of Israel, now
        come down from the cross, so that we may see and believe and trust [in Him]!\u201D
        Those who were crucified with Him were also insulting Him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When the sixth hour (noon) came, darkness covered the whole land
        until the ninth hour (3:00 p.m.). '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And at the ninth hour Jesus cried out with a loud voice, <JESUS>\u201CE</JESUS>loi,
        Eloi, lama sabachthani?\u201D\u2014which is translated, <JESUS>\u201CM</JESUS>y
        God, My God, why have You forsaken Me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Some of the bystanders heard Him and said, \u201CLook! He is calling
        for Elijah!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Someone ran and filled a sponge with sour wine, put it on a reed
        and gave Him a drink, saying, \u201CLet us see whether Elijah is coming to
        take Him down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "But Jesus uttered a loud cry, and breathed out His last [voluntarily,
        sovereignly dismissing and releasing His spirit from His body in submission
        to His Father\u2019s plan]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And the veil [of the Holy of Holies] of the temple was torn in two
        from top to bottom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "When the centurion, who was standing opposite Him, saw the way He
        breathed His last [being fully in control], he said, \u201CTruly this man
        was the Son of God!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Now some women also were watching from a distance, among whom were
        Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the Less and of Joses, and Salome. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: Jesus Is Buried'
      title: Jesus Is Buried
      number: 41
      content: 'When Jesus was in Galilee, they used to accompany him and minister
        to Him; and there were also many other women who came up with Him to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'When evening had already come, because it was the preparation day,
        that is, the day before the Sabbath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Joseph of Arimathea came, a prominent and respected member of the
        Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court), who was himself waiting for the kingdom
        of God\u2014and he courageously dared to go in before Pilate, and asked for
        the body of Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Pilate wondered if He was dead by this time [only six hours after
        being crucified], and he summoned the centurion and asked him whether He
        was already dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And when he learned from the centurion [that Jesus was in fact dead],
        he gave the body to Joseph [by granting him permission to remove it]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'So Joseph purchased a [fine] linen cloth [for wrapping the body],
        and after taking Jesus down [from the cross], he wrapped Him in the linen
        cloth and placed Him in a tomb which had been cut out of rock. Then he rolled
        a [large, wheel-shaped] stone against the entrance of the tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joses were [carefully] watching
        to see where He was laid.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Resurrection'
      title: The Resurrection
      number: 1
      content: '  When the Sabbath was over, Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of James,
        and Salome purchased [sweet-smelling] spices, so that they might go and anoint
        Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Very early on the first day of the week, they came to the tomb when
        the sun had risen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they were saying to one another, \u201CWho will roll back the
        stone for us from the entrance of the tomb?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Looking up, they saw that the stone had been rolled away, though
        it was extremely large. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Entering the tomb, they saw a young man sitting on the right, wearing
        a [long, stately] white robe; and they were amazed and bewildered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CDo not be amazed; you are looking for
        Jesus the Nazarene, who was crucified. He has risen; He is not here. See,
        [here is] the place where they laid Him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But go, tell His disciples and Peter, \u2018He is going ahead of
        you to Galilee; you will see Him there, just as He told you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They went out and fled from the tomb, for they were seized with trembling
        and astonishment; and they said nothing [about it] to anyone, because they
        were afraid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '    [Now Jesus, having risen [from death] early on the first day
        of the week, appeared first to Mary Magdalene, from whom He had cast out
        seven demons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'She went and reported it to those who had been with Him, while they
        were mourning and weeping. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When they heard that He was alive and had been seen by her, they
        did not believe it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'After that, He appeared in a different form to two of them as they
        were walking along the way to the country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Disciples Commissioned'
      title: The Disciples Commissioned
      number: 13
      content: 'They returned [to Jerusalem] and told the others, but they did not
        believe them either.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Later, Jesus appeared to the eleven [disciples] themselves as they
        were reclining at the table; and He called them to account for their unbelief
        and hardness of heart, because they had not believed those who had seen Him
        after He had risen [from death]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CGo into all the world and preach
        the gospel to all creation.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>He who has believed</JESUS> [in Me] <JESUS>and has been baptized
        will be saved</JESUS> [from the penalty of God\u2019s wrath and judgment];
        <JESUS>but he who has not believed will be condemned.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>These signs will accompany those who have believed: in My
        name they will cast out demons, they will speak in new tongues;</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>they will pick up serpents, and if they drink anything deadly,
        it will not hurt them; they will lay hands on the sick, and they will get
        well.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So then, when the Lord Jesus had spoken to them, He was taken up
        into heaven and sat down at the right hand of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And they went out and preached everywhere, while the Lord was working
        with them and confirming the word by the signs that followed.]
      comments: []
